In this game two teams of 5 people battle, controlling a Pokémon each in order to score more points in the enemy goals in a time limit of 10 minutes.\n\nThe most famous esports game of all time is League of Legends, Pokemon Unite is basically a Pokemon based League of Legends with a fun adjustment to the rules.\n\n\n![](https://i.imgur.com/AHTHgVm.gif)\n\n\n# **Our Story**\n\nOur journey began with Proposal 91 in 2022, which marked our entry into the Nouns DAO ecosystem. This pivotal moment allowed us to UNITE as a team under the Nouns banner and pursue competitive excellence in Pokémon UNITE. Over the years, our team has evolved, but our commitment to representing Nouns and pushing boundaries remains unwavering in every part of the world we’ve been to.\n\n\n\n![alt_text](https://i.imgur.com/rxi9V7W.gif "image_tooltip")\n\n\nOur roster is composed of talented players dedicated to success in the competitive scene and building meaningful connections within the community. Pokémon. \n\n\n![](https://i.imgur.com/kEJOEPp.gif)\n\n\n\n## **Our season so far**\n\n\n The season started in November 2024, and we have been having a lot of success! Feb 06 01:16:03 pine-Z790-AORUS-ELITE-AX python[620557]: Tweet data saved successfully: {'tweet_id': '1887384725498548463', 'proposal_title': 'CIP-62: Core Treasury team mandate and funding', 'space_id': 'cow.eth', 'proposal_description': '### Simple Summary\n\nThis CIP proposes to consolidate several existing mandates of the Core Treasury team, originally established by [CIP-19 (karpatkey Proposal to Create a Core Treasury Team)](https://snapshot.box/#/s:cow.eth/proposal/0xc4e9c0a28f12b28aedfc8c3802522a9ac9dd1c7d5045dca94abf555ca2d8cd31) and to request an allocation of 80 million COW tokens to empower the team and karpatkey to pursue additional liquidity provisioning, economic opportunities for the treasury tokens, and funding opportunities for the development and execution of CoW DAO product roadmap over the next 4 years (2025-2028).\n\nThe goal of this CIP is to strategically allocate COW in connection with long-term partners. The Core Treasury team will enact its best judgement on re-allocating COW between different initiatives in order to maximise the funds generated for CoW DAO’s products.\n\nAt the time of writing, we are requesting 80 million COW tokens from the [DAO’s currently owned COW tokens](https://app.safe.global/balances?safe=eth:0xcA771eda0c70aA7d053aB1B25004559B918FE662).\n\n### Motivation\n\nCoW DAO’s products have been revolutionising DeFi and protecting users from MEV since 2022, when the project spun out from GnosisDAO. Since then, CoW Swap & CoW Protocol have facilitated more than $70.8 billion in trading volume, more than $187 billion of value has been protected by MEV Blocker and more than $27 million of volume has been supercharged by CoW AMM’s features.\n\nCoW Swap currently stands as the #1 UI for attracting trading volume, combining unparalleled ease of use with advanced trading tools to deliver an optimal user experience where price improvements are shared with users. CoW Swap & CoW Protocol makes CoW DAO’s products recognized as the largest intent aggregator, seamlessly connecting users to the best trading opportunities, and the second-largest DEX aggregator in Mainnet, enabling efficient and optimized decentralized trades.\n\nAs an innovator in intent-based decentralized exchanges (DEXs), we lead the industry by setting new standards for trading efficiency. Additionally, our pioneering LVR-resistant AMM technology mitigates the risks associated with impermanent loss, providing users with greater stability and profitability.\n\nWe also take pride in being the first RPC provider to reimburse users, offering a groundbreaking approach to incentivizing and supporting our community, ensuring users are rewarded for their engagement and loyalty.\n\nIn addition to these technical and market fit achievements, the team has shown it can also deliver financially, generating 2M net profit for 2024.\n\nThis is why, in order to stay ahead of the innovation curve and keep delivering outstanding products, the team would like to increase the buffer of funds in the treasury, to allow scaling up the core team.\n\nCoW DAO’s innovative products operate on top of sophisticated tokenomics and incentive mechanisms, as highlighted in [CIP-38 - Solver Computed Fees & Rank by Surplus](https://snapshot.box/#/s:cow.eth/proposal/0xfb81daea9be89f4f1c251d53fd9d1481129b97c6f38caaddc42af7f3ce5a52ec) and [CIP-48 - Solver rewards budget renewal and update of CoW DAO bonding pool operations](https://snapshot.box/#/s:cow.eth/proposal/0x563ab9a66265ad72c47a8e55f620f927685dd07d4d49f6d1812905c683f05805).\n\n![2eb66acb5d1827285c8ea04276dbabf41cf736d9_2_561x750.png](ipfs://bafkreieikpueyo5lswnmfrsm33hvsnsjr4gakbmvngnupzaquublb4ecda)\n\nAs depicted in the image above, there is a gap between the revenue accrued by the DAO and the funds received in the Treasury. All operational income generated is first used to reimburse solvers for gas. As there is a weekly gap between fees charged in native tokens, withdrawal in ETH and payment to solvers, a buffer allocation is kept in ETH in the intermediary contracts to ensure correct operation of the protocol. From the net revenue, the Core Treasury team performs COW buybacks (as per [CIP-38 - Solver Computed Fees & Rank by Surplus](https://snapshot.box/#/s:cow.eth/proposal/0xfb81daea9be89f4f1c251d53fd9d1481129b97c6f38caaddc42af7f3ce5a52ec)) and funds the Defense Reserve (vd. [CIP-50 - Establishing a Legal Defense Reserve](https://snapshot.box/#/s:cow.eth/proposal/0xf772608598125f52c1dff6e2386d852845d4e2d44c61ac02946aea6ab5906fa6)). Only the remaining portion of the net revenue is utilised by the Treasury for active DeFi management. For the development of the DAO’s products, a series of functions and tasks must be performed, which have previously been authorised through several CIPs for IT, business development and grants.\n\nPart of the revenue generated by CoW DAO’s products is converted to COW and used to incentivise the solver competition. Nonetheless, a significant part of CoW’s core development work requires funding for other assets.\n\nThis CIP’s intention is to give flexibility to the Treasury to fund the development of the DAO’s products through a new COW token allocation, assuming a continued increase of the amounts to be invested (net of accrued revenue) by 10-20% per year in the period of 2025-2028.\n\nAs outlined in CIP-19, [karpatkey ](http://karpatkey.com)was mandated to create, train, and support a Core Treasury Team. This mandate has been successfully fulfilled, and the Core Treasury Team now comprises members of both the existing Core Team and karpatkey.\n\nThis new CIP seeks to update the mandate of the established Core Treasury Team, building upon the foundation laid by CIP-19 to ensure the continued support of CoW DAO\'s long-term development.\n\n### Specifications\n\nGiven the above, the Core Treasury team requests 80 million COW tokens, that would be allocated to the following initiatives:\n\n* Development of the CoW DAO products - 42M COW\n  * This will cover the majority of the investment plan for the period of 2025-28\n* Defense reserve completion - 5.5M COW\n  * Complete the allocation of [CIP-50 - Establishing a Legal Defense Reserve](https://snapshot.box/#/s:cow.eth/proposal/0xf772608598125f52c1dff6e2386d852845d4e2d44c61ac02946aea6ab5906fa6), ensuring proper funding of the protection layer of the DAO and stop the allocation of part of the DAO’s Revenues\n* Provision of liquidity - 4.5M COW\n  * Increase DEX liquidity (mainly on Mainnet and one additional L2), to ensure proper price discovery in DEX markets, in line with the increasing liquidity on centralised exchanges\n* Solver rewards - 16M COW\n  * An estimated budget for 2025 for the Solver Rewards programs, in line with previous weeks / months ([see example weekly payment here for Mainnet](https://dune.com/cowprotocol/cow-solver-rewards?start_time=2024-12-24+00%3A00%3A00&end_time=2024-12-31+00%3A00%3A00)) and in line with the Growth plan for new networks.\n* Strategic partnerships - 10M COW\n  * This allocation is intended to be used for partnership agreements where CoW DAO\'s products are integrated into other web platforms, with the underlying objective of increasing market share and revenue through revenue sharing, increased volume to the Protocol and/or other economic benefits.\n* Other initiatives - 2M COW\n  * This allocation is intended to perform opportunistic market awareness activities, such as creating incentives for new solver feature development or for token holders.\n\nThe above-mentioned allowances are indicative and flexible, and the Core Treasury team would be mandated to use their best judgment in reallocating funds between each category. For clarity, this means that the total amount requested across all allocations is fixed, but that the amounts allocated to each are what may be changed.\n\n### Listings Mandate\n\nThe Core Treasury Team’s work as part of the CEX listing initiative, led to the COW token being listed by the following venues:\n\n* Coinbase\n* Binance\n* Kraken (Perpetuals)\n* Kucoin\n* Gate.io\n* Bitget\n* Crypto.com\n* HiBT\n* MEXC\n* Bitkan\n* Bitmart\n* ZKE\n* Bybit (Perpetuals)\n\nGiven the success of the listing strategy, and the fact that more venues will be pursued in Q1 2025, the Core Treasury team requests that the remaining funds from the 4M COW budget allocated under [CIP-47 - Funding for the purpose of facilitating the listing COW token on CEXs](https://snapshot.box/#/s:cow.eth/proposal/0x7456f84721dbbe164b30324112accf976ff3be397b1957e68abe6953801a1f97), be fully utilised for the mandate under this CIP. This means that funds which were originally earmarked to be returned to the DAO on 2025-06-31, will remain under this treasury mandate.\n\n### Product Development Mandate\n\nTo clarify the amount of 42M COW earmarked for the development of CoW DAO’s products:\n\n* does not exclude the need for individual service providers or grantees to the DAO to request funding through further CIPs; and\n* is not intended solely to be sold on the open market.\n\nTo ensure the responsible utilisation of COW tokens allocated for the development of the CoW DAO’s products the Core Treasury team proposes the following “guidelines”, with all percentages referring to the portion of the allocation designated for the product development mandate:\n\n* The majority of this allocation cannot be exchanged in the market, and should require limit orders above the previous monthly average price ([provided by CoinGecko](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/cow-protocol/historical_data));\n* To foster collaboration and long-term partnerships, the Core Treasury team may transfer the tokens as follows to entities that can provide substantial long term support to the development and goals of CoW DAO. The Core Treasury team is mandated to pursue the best interest of the DAO and ensure that transactions are done at a higher than market price or at adequate vesting schedules.\n* To maintain a diverse and decentralised ecosystem, no single entity may be transferred more than 3% of the total COW token supply (30M tokens) under these mandates.\n\n### Text edited to fit into Snapshot chars limit. Please refer to the forum post for the whole text, specially the "Additional Terms" section.', 'dao_name': 'coW DAO'}

Feb 06 05:17:55 pine-Z790-AORUS-ELITE-AX python[620557]: Tweet data saved successfully: {'tweet_id': '1887445595238916138', 'proposal_title': '[ARBITRUM] Approve the Nova Fee Sweep Action', 'space_id': 'eventhorizongitcoin.eth', 'proposal_description': '## Abstract\nThe Nova Fee Sweep action applies to historical Nova transaction fees currently held in the [L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a); these fees will be swept into the DAO Treasury with the use of the modernized fee collection infrastructure outlined in the [Nova Fee Router Proposal](https://snapshot.box/#/s:arbitrumfoundation.eth/proposal/0x4ad37b12ffe5c334e0c19113ac54222983e18d36a255fbde60e483592f35fc65). The full balance of ETH–currently 1,885 ETH–will be transferred to the DAO Treasury on Arbitrum One using established smart contract infrastructure.\n\nThere will be an upcoming AIP which combines both the Timeboost AIP and the Nova Fee Sweep action AIP into a single proposal for an on-chain vote on Tally. If the on-chain vote on Tally passes successfully, Timeboost will be enabled on Arbitrum One and Arbitrum Nova and the Nova Fee Sweep action will be executed. This temperature check serves as a way for the DAO to explicitly approve for the fees from the historical [L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a) to the [ChildToParentRouter](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0x36d0170d92f66e8949eb276c3ac4fea64f83704d#code).\n\n## Motivation\nHistorically, Nova transaction fees accumulated to the [L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a) address, which required a lengthy constitutional proposal process for the ArbitrumDAO to access or spend. The successful passing of the [Nova Fee Router proposal](https://www.tally.xyz/gov/arbitrum/proposal/108288822474129076868455956066667369439381709547570289793612729242368710728616) redirected these fees to a system of "fee routers" that automatically transfers funds to the ArbitrumDAO treasury, reducing quorum requirements, reducing delays, and simplifying accounting by consolidating funds directly in the treasury. As of 28 August 2024, Nova transaction fees began accumulating to a series of RewardDistributor contracts as outlined in the Nova Fee Router proposal, streamlining the revenue collection process for the DAO.\n\nHowever, transaction fees that accumulated to the L1TimelockAlias *before* the Nova Fee Router change went into effect remain in the L1TimelockAlias, totalling 1,885.79 ETH. This proposal intends to sweep these historical Nova transaction fees from the legacy L1TimelockAlias address into the new fee collection system. This will be a one-time task because funds collected after 28 August 2024 have been, and will continue to be, automatically forwarded through the new fee collection system to the ArbitrumDAO treasury.\n\n## Key Terms\n[L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a): address that historically accumulated Nova transaction fees but was replaced by RewardDistributor contracts as a part of the [Nova Fee Router Proposal](https://snapshot.box/#/s:arbitrumfoundation.eth/proposal/0x4ad37b12ffe5c334e0c19113ac54222983e18d36a255fbde60e483592f35fc65) to upgrade the fee collection infrastructure; historical fees held by this address are the subject of this proposal. \n\n[ChildToParentRouter](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0x36d0170d92f66e8949eb276c3ac4fea64f83704d#code): smart contract that, when called, creates an L2-to-L1 message which sends the contract’s full ETH balance; once the message is executed, the ETH is transferred to a ParentToChildRouter smart contract on L1\n\n[ParentToChildRouter](https://etherscan.io/address/0x40cd7d713d7ae463f95ce5d342ea6e7f5cf7c999#code): smart contract that, when called, creates a retryable ticket which transfers the contract’s full ETH balance from L1 to the DAO Treasury on Arbitrum One\n\nThe full script for executing the Nova Fee Sweep can be found here: [Standalone Nova Fee Sweep Proposal #303](https://github.com/ArbitrumFoundation/governance/pull/303)\n\n## Steps to Implement\nThe script will be included alongside the onchain AIP which proposes for the adoption of Timeboost on Tally. Since both changes are bundled into one onchain AIP, this temperature check serves as a way for the DAO to explicitly approve for the fees from the historical [L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a) to the [ChildToParentRouter](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0x36d0170d92f66e8949eb276c3ac4fea64f83704d#code).\n\nOnce transaction fees are received by the ChildToParentRouter, the automated fee collection process will be activated, forwarding fees to the [ParentToChildRouter](https://etherscan.io/address/0x40cd7d713d7ae463f95ce5d342ea6e7f5cf7c999#code) on L1 and eventually to the [DAO Treasury](https://arbiscan.io/address/0xf3fc178157fb3c87548baa86f9d24ba38e649b58) on Arbitrum One; complete implementation details for this automated fee routing can be found in the [preceding Tally proposal](https://www.tally.xyz/gov/arbitrum/proposal/108288822474129076868455956066667369439381709547570289793612729242368710728616). Please note that Reward Distributor contracts are irrelevant for this particular action as historical fees from the L1TimelockAlias will be transferred directly to the ChildToParentRouter.\n\n## Resources and Timelines:\n[Timeboost + Nova Fee Sweep AIP forum post](https://forum.arbitrum.foundation/t/aip-timeboost-nova-fee-sweep/28247) \nNova Fee Sweep Snapshot: 30 Jan - 6 Feb\n\nThe Arbitrum Foundation will communicate a tentative date for the creation of the onchain AIP in the near future.\n\n\n\nhttps://snapshot.org/#/arbitrumfoundation.eth/proposal/0xbd77b4faf99e06c7b4117e5dafaf5bb8f873bcffbb5c9d414a7ff745b6849f3a', 'dao_name': 'Gitcoin'}

Feb 06 07:18:45 pine-Z790-AORUS-ELITE-AX python[620557]: Tweet data saved successfully: {'tweet_id': '1887476006706934147', 'proposal_title': "Bolstering Moonwell's Safety Module: Rewarding Stakers via Reserve Auctions", 'space_id': 'moonwell-governance.eth', 'proposal_description': "## **Summary**\nThis proposal is a continuation of [MIP-X05](https://moonwell.fi/governance/proposal/moonbeam?id=140), and aims to further enhance governance participation and bolster Moonwell's Safety Module by directing excess protocol revenue toward staking rewards. Currently, Moonwell generates significant protocol revenue, with $386.1K in revenue and over $2.1M in fees for lenders in December 2024 alone. However, this revenue remains idle as reserves in the core markets.\nWe would like to propose an **onchain auction system** where excess protocol revenue is auctioned for WELL tokens, which are then allocated to the Safety Module Ecosystem Reserve. This approach will:\n- **Increase staking rewards for WELL stakers in the Safety Module**\n- **Enhance security through greater shortfall insurance and fostering stronger governance engagement**\n- **Encourage continued governance participation**\nWe seek to gauge community sentiment through this snapshot temperature check vote before moving forward with an onchain vote in the next week. Please also review the [associated forum post](https://forum.moonwell.fi/t/increasing-governance-participation-and-rewarding-voters-part-2/1525/) for additional details and to share any thoughts, questions, or concerns that you may have.\n---\n## **Moonwell Protocol Revenue Generation**\n### **Current Revenue Growth**\nMoonwell is one of the **top revenue-generating protocols** across all deployed networks. In December 2024 alone, the protocol generated **$386.1K in revenue** and over **$2.1M in fees for lenders.** Until now, that protocol revenue has been largely idle, stored in **core markets as reserves**, which act as extra liquidity to facilitate user withdrawals.\n![Revenue Chart](https://europe1.discourse-cdn.com/flex017/uploads/moonwell/original/2X/6/6d8c545e04699ff1aad8d05f45ab79e4e0a6da56.png)\n### **New Sources of Revenue**\nNew revenue sources have come online in recent weeks and months that should continue to increase protocol revenue, primarily in three areas:\n- **Vault Performance Fees:** Moonwell’s Flagship and Frontier vaults generate performance fees, captured as protocol revenue and added to core market reserves. The retail borrowing demand for USDC from Coinbase Bitcoin borrowers is expected to significantly increase these fees in the coming months as their new borrow product continues to be rolled out to more users.\n- **Oracle Extracted Value (OEV):** A [pilot for Oracle Extracted Value](https://moonwell.fi/governance/proposal/moonbeam?id=153) launched on Optimism. Once proven successful, it will be put up to a vote to expand to Base and Optimism markets, significantly increasing protocol revenue. According to [IntoTheBlock data](https://defirisk.intotheblock.com/metrics/base/moonwell), liquidators have made **$2.09M in profit from Base core market liquidations alone**. With the new OEV solution, **99% of that could be recognized as protocol revenue**.\n- **Leveraged Bitcoin Restaking Markets:** New markets for Lombard BTC and the cbBTC Frontier vault have positioned Moonwell as the **premier venue for leveraged Bitcoin restaking**, increasing TVL and revenue in the coming months.\n### **Why This Matters**\nMoonwell has focused relentlessly on **capital efficiency, fee capture, and revenue growth**. Notably, much of Morpho’s TVL originates from Moonwell’s vaults, though DeFi Llama does not attribute that TVL to Moonwell. However, what truly matters is capital efficiency and revenue generation, and Moonwell generates more revenue per $ of TVL than any other lending app on Base.\n## **Where Should This Revenue Go?**\n### **The Case for Safety Module Rewards**\nFor years, DeFi protocols have debated how to allocate excess revenue effectively. Many options carry excessive regulatory risk, making them unfeasible. After months of consultation with top legal experts, Moonwell contributors have come up with what we believe to be a sustainable mechanism that aligns all stakeholder incentives.\nAs a continuation of the effort to increase governance participation, we propose that **excess protocol revenue be auctioned for WELL tokens and allocated to the Safety Module Ecosystem Reserve.**The Ecosystem Reserve is a smart contract that holds protocol reserves and is currently used to reward [Safety Module](https://docs.moonwell.fi/moonwell/moonwell-overview/stake) stakers for their role in shortfall insurance and governance participation.\nTo achieve this, Moonwell contributors propose implementing **onchain auctions** via smart contracts:\n- Excess ETH, USDC, cbBTC, wstETH, cbETH, rETH, AERO, and other reserves will be auctioned for WELL.\n- The acquired WELL will be transferred to the Safety Module Ecosystem Reserve to bolster staking rewards.\n---\n### **How the Auction System Works**\nThis system introduces a new **onchain auction contract** that allows WELL tokens to be used in exchange for reserve assets. The contract will conduct **multiple mini-auctions** throughout each cycle, selling reserve assets over time. This approach:\n- **Averages out sale prices** over time, effectively emulating a TWAP (Time-Weighted Average Price) strategy.\n- Uses a **linear decay function** that initially applies a **premium**, then gradually introduces a **discount** relative to the Chainlink price.\n- **Caches prices** at each step to ensure a structured, predictable auction process.\n- Sends proceeds to the **WELL Holding contract**, which can then be used to fund the **Safety Module via governance proposals.**\n### **Step-by-Step Walkthrough**\nHere’s how the process will work:\n![Auction Overview](https://europe1.discourse-cdn.com/flex017/uploads/moonwell/optimized/2X/1/1e6bbcc7e72841f4e76ccc83c36d242fdaee2e0f_2_1380x812.png)\n1. **Automated Governance Proposal:** The governance proposal that rebalances liquidity incentives will include additional calls to withdraw excess protocol revenue to the Governor smart contract.\n   - While the example focuses on WETH and USDC, this process applies to all relevant markets.\n2. **Token Transfer to Auction Contracts:** The same governance proposal will transfer WETH, USDC, and other tokens to separate auction contracts for each asset, initiating a fully onchain, decentralized auction.\n   - Auctions begin with 100% of the assets (WETH, USDC, etc.), and by the end of a two-week period, they will be converted to 100% WELL.\n3. **Auction Mechanics:**\n   - The total auctioned tokens are divided into 84 equal mini-auctions, each lasting 4 hours.\n   - Each mini-auction starts above the Chainlink price and slowly decays over 4 hours until a market participant (typically a MEV bot) swaps WELL for the asset.\n   - By splitting the auction into 84 time-weighted auctions, the system ensures optimal price execution while avoiding unnecessary swap fees and gas costs.\n4. **Final Settlement & Distribution:**\n   - Four weeks later (two weeks after the auctions end), the next automated liquidity incentive proposal will transfer the acquired WELL to the Safety Module Ecosystem Reserve.\n   - Governance will then adjust the staking rate to enable the higher staking reward APR.\n5. **Claiming Staking Rewards:**\n   - Safety Module stakers can claim rewards at any time, as they do currently.\n   - No structural changes to the Safety Module architecture are proposed—the Ecosystem Reserve was designed for this purpose.\n### **Determining Safe Reserve Withdrawal Levels**\nA key question is **how much of each market's reserves should be allocated to these auctions?**\n- Input from Gauntlet and other risk experts is critical in establishing safe reserve thresholds for each core market.\n- These thresholds should be dynamic—if market conditions shift significantly, Gauntlet and other contributors can provide updated guidance, which can then be reflected in governance reward speed proposals.\n---\n## **Projected Impact on Staking Rewards**\nHow much would this bolster Safety Module staking rewards?\n![Staking Rewards Impact](https://europe1.discourse-cdn.com/flex017/uploads/moonwell/optimized/2X/f/fd2d81a733ce9aa14ff9025c4611b8d451adfad3_2_1380x700.png)\n- In **December 2024**, the [automated liquidity incentives proposal](https://moonwell.fi/governance/proposal/moonbeam?id=150) allocated **4,394,963.08 WELL** to Safety Module stakers on Base.\n  - At today’s price of **$0.039**, that equates to **~$171,403.56 in rewards** and a **7.42% APR.**\n- In **December 2024,** Moonwell also generated **~$352,777** in protocol revenue on Base, according to [Token Terminal](https://tokenterminal.com/explorer/studio/dashboards/e713fb3f-c10b-45ed-93d4-4e48779dd849).\nRedirecting protocol revenue to **Safety Module stakers could increase staking rewards by an estimated 3.06x, boosting APR to 22.71%.**\n> **Note:** Estimates are subject to market conditions and may vary.\n---\n## Open Questions\n* For Gauntlet, BlockAnalitica, B. Protocol, and other risk-focused contributors: what should we keep in each market as a healthy level of reserves?\n* Should we fully distribute all the WELL obtained through the auctions to Safety Module stakers every 4 weeks, or should the staking APR be capped at some lower level, such as 20%?\n  * Some contributors have proposed capping the staking APR at 20%, which would allow some WELL to stay in the Safety Module Ecosystem Reserve, which would be beneficial to keep the staking APR high during bear markets, or to further bolster the shortfall insurance.\n* What challenges or issues do you see with this proposal?\n---\n## **Voting Options**\n✅ **Yay** – Support implementing the above model to auction excess protocol reserves into staking rewards, strengthening governance participation and shortfall insurance.\n❌**Nay** – Do not implement this change.\n⚪**Abstain** – No preference on the decision.", 'dao_name': 'Moonwell'}

Feb 06 09:19:51 pine-Z790-AORUS-ELITE-AX python[620557]: Tweet data saved successfully: {'tweet_id': '1887506479927701926', 'proposal_title': 'The Imperative to Limit Excessive Voting Power Held by a Co-Founder', 'space_id': 'snapshot.dcl.eth', 'proposal_description': "> by 0xbc02db030361121dd43bbb2fcbcb4f9f98c1dc7d (JasonX)\n\nThe concentration of 8.5 million VP (Voting Power) in the hands of Mr. Esteban, a co-founder of Decentraland, fundamentally undermines the principles of decentralized governance and community-driven decision-making that are core to the platform's founding ethos. This disproportionate control not only creates a de facto veto over proposals—including grants, polls, governance changes, and hiring decisions—but also poses significant legal and ethical challenges, particularly regarding SEC regulations and conflicts of interest.\n\n\\*\\*1. Conflict of Interest and Undermining Community Governance\n\\*\\*Decentraland was envisioned as a community-owned, community-driven platform where decisions would reflect the collective will rather than be dominated by a select few. However, when a single co-founder holds overwhelming VP, it enables him to unilaterally alter outcomes, effectively sidelining community input. This concentration of power constitutes a clear conflict of interest, placing personal control above the collective interests of the community. Such a scenario starkly contradicts the foundational values of decentralization and transparency that are essential to the project’s credibility and long-term viability.\n\n\\*\\*2. Legal Implications and SEC Considerations\n\\*\\*Legally, this situation raises serious concerns under SEC guidelines and broader securities laws. Regulatory bodies such as the SEC scrutinize governance structures that allow the manipulation of outcomes affecting market and investor interests. In this case, the singular voting power of a co-founder could be interpreted as a breach of fiduciary duty, wherein personal interests conflict with those of the broader investor community. SEC oversight increasingly emphasizes the need for decentralized platforms to maintain fair and transparent governance structures that prevent insider manipulation. The potential for one individual to override community consensus may attract regulatory action and lead to legal consequences, particularly if such power is misused to benefit a select few at the expense of the broader community.\n\n\\*\\*3. Violation of Core Decentraland Principles\n\\*\\*Decentraland’s identity as a community-centric platform is built on the promise of democratized decision-making and equitable influence. Allowing a co-founder to retain such overwhelming voting power not only betrays that promise but also transforms the platform into an environment of centralized power. This centralization risks alienating community members and undermining trust in the project’s governance model. By subverting the intended distributed authority, the platform jeopardizes its core identity, with potential long-term implications for user engagement and its reputation in the evolving digital asset ecosystem.\n\n\\*\\*4. Recommendations for Reform\n\\*\\*To preserve the integrity of Decentraland's governance and align with both community expectations and regulatory standards, it is imperative to mitigate this concentration of power. Possible measures include:\n\nImplementing Vesting Schedules or Voting Caps: Establish limits on the maximum voting power any single entity or individual may hold.\nIntroducing Decentralized Safeguards: Require a supermajority or the involvement of independent third parties for critical proposals.\nRegular Audits and Transparency Reports: Conduct independent audits to monitor voting power distribution and ensure compliance with both internal policies and external regulatory guidelines.\n\n\\*\\*Conclusion\nAllowing Mr. Esteban to wield such significant VP creates a clear conflict of interest and directly contravenes the foundational principles of community governance upon which Decentraland was built. The potential for unilateral decision-making raises red flags from both ethical and legal perspectives, inviting scrutiny from regulatory bodies such as the SEC. For the sake of preserving the platform’s democratic ethos and ensuring long-term sustainability, it is both necessary and urgent to reconsider the extent of voting power granted to any single individual—particularly a co-founder. This approach safeguards community interests and aligns Decentraland with best practices in decentralized governance and regulatory compliance.\n\nThis proposal got taken down becuase of cencorship & other political reasons, which is why I am re-submitting it today. I am only sharing my views & opinions & I believe as a platform contributor, stakeholder, asset holder & a long time community member I deserve the right to express my views. If for any reasons this proposal gets taken down once more , I will be pursuing legal actions.\n\nShould we limite excessive voting power held by a co-founder?\n\n- Yes\n- No\n- Invalid question/options\n\n\n**[This proposal is summarized due to technical limitations. If they qualify, **Nouns stands to financially benefit!**\n\nChanges from Prop 715:\n\n- 12 Months → 6 Months   \n- Added plan to return revenue to DAO through sticker sales.   \n- Narrowed scope to focus on Major results and organizing around the event.   \n- Budget reworked and significantly slimmed. \n\n---\n\n## Request Overview\n\nWe are asking NounsDAO to front six months of operational expenses for the Nouns CS2 team as we embark on the journey to qualify for the Austin Major in June 2025. This event is more than just a tournament—it’s a chance to secure a spot in Counter-Strike history, represent Nouns on one of the world’s biggest stages, and generate sustainable revenue for the DAO’s future operations.\n\n![CS Team Players](https://i.ibb.co/vjLn8g2/newbanner5.png)\n\nIf the team qualifies for the Major, **25% of generated sticker revenue will return to the DAO (estimated at $200,000 – $500,000).**\n\nThis gives the DAO all of the traditional benefits of our operating rosters in mass-exposure and onboarding, as well as a very unique financial incentive on top. For the remaining sticker revenue, 50% (industry standard) will go to the players and the remaining 25% will be used to extend the runway of Nouns CS, aiming to secure another Major appearance in December.\n\n![Revenue Flowchat](https://i.ibb.co/9r9jBWM/bannerv3.png)\n\nThese funds will be returned to the DAO either through the purchase of a single noun (to avoid any concerns of a governance balance shift), or through a direct transfer via the new DUNA entity after coordinating with the DUNA admin.\n\n---\n\n## What is Sticker Sales Revenue?\n\nIn Counter-Strike, teams that qualify for the Major receive custom, in-game team stickers that anyone can purchase, trade, and collect. These stickers are a cherished part of the community, immortalizing the teams in-game all while providing a significant and sustainable revenue stream. Think of these as Counter-Strike NFT\'s.\n\nThe figures for these stickers have ranged from mid six-figures up to millions in the past.\n\n---\n\n## Why Is This Significant?\n\n### The Power of Stickers in Counter-Strike\n\n![Nouns Sticker Gif](https://i.ibb.co/6YG3dQn/CS-Prop-Sticker.gif "Example of in-game sticker with our logo")\n\nSecuring our spot at the Major means we’ll have Nounish-themed stickers in the game—a permanent, collectible representation of our team and our brand.\n\nPlayers bond very closely with their collected skins, developing a fandom for the teams that the stickers represent, to the point of there being X accounts that showcase sticker "crafts" where a player has decorated their weapon with stickers. \n\nStickers will help Nouns further integrate into the culture while bringing unparalleled brand awareness to a dedicated community of over 30 million monthly players.\n\n![Splitter](https://i.ibb.co/NYzJFxw/upload-9605bafa106f5fc715565d5d229c2d11.png)\n\n### The 2025 Austin Major\n\n![Paris Major Crowd](https://i.ibb.co/WVgWkjQ/blastcrowd2.png "Crowd at the 2023 BLAST Paris Major")\n\nTens of thousands will gather this year to witness the Austin Major in Austin, Texas—a significant event for Nouns Esports and the culture of Counter-Strike as the worlds top 32 teams from around the globe go head-to-head!\n\nAs one of the few all-North American teams, we have a rare and meaningful opportunity to qualify for the first Major on home soil in seven years. Made all the more special as it comes after North America’s only Major victory at the Boston Major back in 2018.\n\nWe\'ll be keeping our eyes out for any opportunities to promote Nouns and run events/activations centered around the Major as it draws closer.\n\n![Splitter](https://i.ibb.co/NYzJFxw/upload-9605bafa106f5fc715565d5d229c2d11.png)\n\n### Major Viewership\n\n![Major Viewership Stats](https://i.ibb.co/GnmzdJH/viewership8.png)\n\nCounter-Strike reigns as one of the most watched esports on the planet, being religiously followed by millions with Majors seeing the greatest peaks of viewership and cumulative watch hours year after year.\n\nThe coming major in Austin is expected to hold strong and put up similar, if not better, viewership numbers exposing Nouns to more eyes than ever before within the space.\n\n---\n\n## How Do We Qualify for the Major?\n\nA Major features 32 slots, with 11 allocated to our region, the Americas. Teams are ranked using a new points system, and based on our historical performance and current ranking, we are eligible to compete for these spots.\n\n![Path to the Major](https://i.ibb.co/m8Gxg8N/pathv5.png)\n\nThis is nearly double the number of slots our region has traditionally received. Instead of going through two separate qualifiers as in the past, we will now have a single qualifier against our regional competition for a direct spot in the Major. If we do not receive a direct invite North America should have 3 dedicated slots for qualification.\n\n---\n\n## How Likely Are We to Qualify?\n\nThis year sees some drastic changes to the distribution of major spots, as well as quantity of participating teams. With these new rules we feel it is more likely than ever that our team will qualify for the upcoming Austin Major based on our historical performance and quality of the roster assembled.\n\n![CS Team Gif](https://i.ibb.co/gyfJpj1/CS-Mens.gif)\n\nWe are very confident in our ability to secure one of these spots, as we have proven ourselves against similar competition time after time in the past. During the previous Major qualification cycle, we achieved a flawless 3-0 record against North American teams in the qualifier to the Regional Major Rankings event (RMR), which included a mix of the region\'s top talent.\n\n![CS Team Pictures](https://i.ibb.co/bvd9X5n/nogplayers3.png)\n\nAdditionally we believe in this path based on our historical performance against domestic competition, the quality of the team we have assembled (some saying our best roster to date), and our [Intel Grand Slam](https://www.espn.com/esports/story/_/id/27148934/intel-grand-slam-latest-achievement-team-liquid-banner-year) winning coach [adreN](https://x.com/adreN_Hoag) who after a year with Nouns, understands the dynamics and workings of the DAO. We believe in him to be the figurehead leading our team to the Major.\n\n---\n\n## Budget Overview\n\n![Budget Overview](https://i.ibb.co/qWnR4Y3/newerbudget.png)\n\nTotal Budget: **$218,000 USDC**\n\n![Splitter](https://i.ibb.co/NYzJFxw/upload-9605bafa106f5fc715565d5d229c2d11.png)\n\n**Support Staff:**\n\n- **$20,000** — Manager   \n- **$15,500** — Graphic Designer \n\n\u200b**Team Budget:**\n\n- **$36,000** — Coach   \n- **$20,800 / Player** — 5 Players    \n- **$35,000** — Bootcamps and LAN Event Travel   \n- **$7,500** — Misc.\n  \u200b \u200b \u200b \u200b ⦁ Analytics Software\n  \u200b \u200b \u200b \u200b ⦁ Practice Server\n  \u200b \u200b \u200b \u200b ⦁ Nounish Jerseys\n  \u200b \u200b \u200b \u200b ⦁ Noggles \n\n![Splitter](https://i.ibb.co/NYzJFxw/upload-9605bafa106f5fc715565d5d229c2d11.png)\n\nmultisig — **Machimus.eth**, **adreN.eth**, and **nounsesports.eth**\n\n![Splitter](https://i.ibb.co/NYzJFxw/upload-9605bafa106f5fc715565d5d229c2d11.png)\n\n## CS FANS ♥ NOUNS — Community Reception to First Prop\n\nCS fans from around the globe made their voices heard after learning about our initial prop, check them out! ↓\n\n[![Testimonials](https://i.ibb.co/Qn0JRMV/testimontials-2.gif "https://www.figma.com/design/j57qDWYETPLVdqDzOrnZay/CS-FANS-%E2%99%A5-NOUNS?node-id=0-1&p=f")](https://www.figma.com/design/j57qDWYETPLVdqDzOrnZay/CS-FANS-%E2%99%A5-NOUNS?node-id=0-1&p=f)', 'dao_name': 'N/A'}

Feb 06 15:26:52 pine-Z790-AORUS-ELITE-AX python[620557]: Tweet data saved successfully: {'tweet_id': '1887598842356404253', 'proposal_title': 'Reduce ACX emissions to ACX LPs', 'space_id': 'acrossprotocol.eth', 'proposal_description': '**Author(s):** ACX Emissions Committee (Kevin Chan, David Korpi, Ryan Carman, Dylan O’Reilly, Chase Coleman)\n**Status:** Proposed\n**Related Discussions:** [Previous Snapshot Proposal](https://snapshot.org/#/s:acrossprotocol.eth/proposal/0x41950ecbed593e4f7f02b12627ee19a75671c157ed7b36b2473073e3ae02cb4a), [Reduce ACX emissions forum post](https://forum.across.to/t/reduce-acx-emissions-for-acx-lps-wbtc-lps-and-wsteth-acx-lps/1977), [Emissions committee](https://forum.across.to/t/acx-emissions-committee/1787)\n---\n\n### Summary:\n\nThe Across DAO should decrease ACX emissions for Across ACX LPs. The ACX liquidity pools are rewarded a high APY in comparison to the utilization of the asset or necessity of the emissions. The ACX Emissions Committee only has permissions and a framework to control ACX emissions for ETH, USDC, USDT, and DAI. We are putting together this one-off proposal to decrease ACX emissions in a similar way to ETH, USDC, USDT, and DAI. A similar proposal was made in August 2024; however, it failed to pass due to circumstances at the time. Given much healthier liquidity in the ACX token and strong fundamentals, it makes sense to revisit this proposal now. Reducing unnecessary ACX emissions will alleviate potential selling pressure from this excess supply of ACX tokens.\n\n### Motivation:\n\nThe Across DAO should optimally manage ACX emissions for all liquidity it incentivizes. One way that we have done this previously is by creating the ACX Emissions Committee (AEC). The AEC uses a transparent and restrictive framework to adjust emissions awarded to Across ETH/USDC/USDT/DAI LPs. The framework monitors the utilization and comparable yield alternatives of each asset to make ACX emissions adjustments. Across ACX LPs were excluded from the AEC\'s purview because there are no comparable yield alternatives for ACX and there are other considerations for this asset when we think about the "optimal" ACX emissions for this asset.\n\nACX emissions for ACX LPs were initially set high to incentivize ACX airdrop recipients to not immediately sell their tokens and to get these token holders familiar with the reward locking mechanism. It’s been over 2 years since the launch of the token and the current level of emissions is not necessary. These emissions were reduced over a year ago, but a further reduction is now necessary. ACX utilization consistently sits close to zero given a lack of bridging needs. Yet, the emissions rate for the ACX LP is by far the highest at 26.3k ACX per day. This is over one third of all daily emissions and nearly exceeds the sum of emissions being used for ETH, USDC, USDT, and DAI - assets that are heavily bridged on Across.\n\nThe bottomline is that the Across DAO should decrease ACX LP base emissions by 50% from 15k ACX per day to 7.5k ACX per day.\n\n### Specification & Implementation: \n\nThe ACX LP emissions are currently 15,000 ACX per day. Our proposal is to lower this to 7,500 ACX per day. If approved, this will be implemented by the AEC.\n\n\n### Rationale:\n\nRationale is described above. Please also reference the logic from Dylan\'s comment on the [forum thread](https://forum.across.to/t/reduce-acx-emissions-for-acx-lps-wbtc-lps-and-wsteth-acx-lps/1977/8).\n\n\n### Downside (Cons):\n\nAs highlighted in the discussion forum, there is the potential that some ACX LPs withdraw their funds and sell -- The AEC believes that this will be a relatively muted effect as the ACX LPs are still receiving a significant amount of emissions. In addition, the liquidity of the ACX token has significantly increased as multiple large centralized exchanges have listed ACX since this reduction was last proposed. As an illustration, the 30 day average daily ACX volume since August 2024 has increased from ~$1mm/day to over $30mm/day today. The market should be able to absorb any weak holders of ACX and should be better at efficiently representing the fundamental value of Across protocol.\n\n\n### Voting:\n\nA yes vote means that you would like to decrease the ACX emissions being paid to ACX LPs from 15,000 ACX/day to 7,500 ACX/day.\n\nA no vote means that you would like the ACX emissions being paid to ACX LPs to stay the same.', 'dao_name': 'Across'}

It is designed to optimize liquidity utilization while maintaining full compatibility with Ethereum's execution environment.\n\nKey Features:\n* EVM-Identical Execution – Fully mirrors the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM), ensuring compatibility with all Ethereum dApps, RPC endpoints, and network upgrades.\n* Tri-Token System – The network operates with three distinct tokens:\nBERA – The primary transaction and fee token.\nBGT – The governance token distributed to liquidity providers.\nHONEY – A stablecoin used for collateral-backed transactions.\n* BeaconKit Framework – A modular EVM-focused consensus client developed by Berachain, integrating CometBFT for features like single-slot finality (SSF) and enhanced composability.\n* DeFi-Centric Design – Liquidity staking ensures that assets remain liquid and usable while still securing the network.\n\nOriginally emerging as an NFT project (Bong Bears), Berachain has since evolved into a full-scale blockchain ecosystem. \n\nThe Berachain mainnet is set to launch on February 6, 2025.\n\n# Proposal\n\n* Enable support for Berachain within the Symbiosis protocol. The integration includes the following steps:\n* Deploying and tuning Symbiosis contracts on Berachain to ensure smooth operation.\n* Adding tokens for Berachain in the Symbiosis AMM DEX on the host chain: WETH.\n* Leveraging existing DEXs on Berachain to enable on-chain routing.\n* Activating the Symbiosis relayers network to work with the new blockchain.\n\n# Key Points\n* **The launch of Berachain mainnet** is expected to generate high community engagement and liquidity flow, making early integration into Symbiosis strategically valuable.\n* **Proof-of-Liquidity (PoL)** introduces a new paradigm for blockchain networks. With this additional funding, the available funds at the discretion of the Grant Committee to give out for funds in 2025 is 600,000 xDAI and 1,465,260 COW for Grant activities and 4,990,000 COW for volume grants.\n\nThe use of grants in the CoW ecosystem is a critical driver for fostering innovation and growth. Grants not only incentivize builders to develop on top of CoW but also encourage the creation of impactful products that align with the ecosystem’s goals. Since the inception of the Grants DAO, the initiative has successfully onboarded several impactful projects that have significantly advanced the CoW ecosystem, contributing positively to its expansion and overall utility.\n\n# Motivation\n\nThe CoW Grants Program has funded numerous impactful projects contributing to the CoW ecosystem. For a full list and details on their contributions, please refer to the forum [post](https://forum.cow.fi/t/cip-draft-renewing-the-cow-grants-program/2771).\n\n# Grant program financial position\n\n![financial.png](ipfs://bafkreibpep3htrulwaeijzdnrnw3fqqk2uafx2rlvvcemyvgg3gdzt667m)\n\nConsidering since the Grants program was created:\n\n-   **Payouts Completed**: So far, the Grants DAO has distributed a total of 919,853.03 xDAI and 2,602,740 COW, of which 1,010,000 COW was for the Volume program.\n-   **Total Commitments**: The Committee has committed 922,597.69 xDAI and 1,661,500 COW to various projects and initiatives. These commitments account for 51.26% of the xDAI budget, 53.60% of the COW budget, and 16.83% of the COW Volume allocation.\n-   **Volume-Based Grants**: Of the 6,000,000 COW allocated for volume-based grants, 16.83% has been committed. To date, multiple milestones have been met, and payouts have been made to eligible projects under this category.\n\nThe above allocations lead to a free funds allocation, from the prior CIP mandate of 198,803 xDAI, 1,1465,260 COW, and 4,990,000 COW allocated for Volume-Based Grants.\n\nGiven the above remaining allocation, which will continue to be available for Grant allocation via the Grants DAO committee, the Grants DAO committee requests under this CIP for the following additional funding:\n\n1. An extra allocation of 383,000 xDAI (to initiate the year with a full budget of 600,000 xDAI;\n2. The power to allocate part of the CoW Volume budget to non-volume CoW grants.\n\nThe xDAI funds should be sent by the Core Treasury team to the Grants DAO Safe (gno:0xDA00000B30dCf0C3f5d968e4451Ebdee6950d63e) in two instalments:\n\n1. On passing of this CIP: 183,000 xDAI\n2. By Jul 2025: 200,000 xDAI\n\n## Bonus Allocation for Grants\n\nGrantees who exceed expectations, contribute significantly to the CoW ecosystem, or deliver exceptional results may receive a discretionary bonus of up to 10,000 xDAI (or equivalent in COW). Bonuses are awarded solely by the committee and do not require a Snapshot vote.\n\nA portion of the Grants DAO budget is allocated for these bonuses. Once exhausted, further bonuses require approval via an on-chain vote.\n\nFor detailed criteria and process, please refer to the forum [post](https://forum.cow.fi/t/cip-draft-renewing-the-cow-grants-program/2771).\n\n## Continuation of Existing Grant Commitments\n\nAll grants that have been committed within the current mandate but extend beyond the end of the term (January 31, 2026) will remain valid and honored under this CIP. This ensures that grantees fulfilling their milestones in 2026 will still receive their allocated funding, regardless of whether the Grants DAO program is renewed beyond this term. Any such outstanding payments will continue to be administered by the Grants DAO Committee or, in the event of dissolution, transferred to CoW DAO for fulfillment.\n\n\n## CoW Grants Committee Structure and Operations\n\n### Committee Composition\n\nThe **CoW Grants Committee** comprises five members:  \n- **2 Core Team Members**  \n- **3 Community Members**\n\nThe committee operates as a Gnosis Safe with a 4/5 quorum required for approving grants. Each member is responsible for overseeing multiple grants and serving as a steward for assigned grants. They guide grantees through the entire process, from onboarding to grant completion.\n\n### Committee Members and Wallet Addresses\n- **Community Members:**\n  - @Kubesqrt - `0x177127622c4A00F3d409B75571e12cB3c8973d3c`\n  - @Chim9 - `0xF44217A8b6b3f258BFFEaD635c226528aa516aea`\n  - @mfw78 - `0x0F641723997145715d23c0129b96041011d26666`\n  \n- **Core Team Members:**\n  - @middleway.eth - `0xa11da8b2d9a7883eb636d7de426025e5fd9fda1a`\n  - @Master_CoW - `0x76ba9825a5f707f133124e4608f1f2dd1ef4006a`\n\n\n## Governance and Safe Operations\n\n### Nested Safe Design\nThe CoW Grants DAO has historically used a nested safe design, enabling the DAO to retain full control of funds. However, this structure introduced operational inefficiencies in handling transactions.\n\n### Proposed Update\nTo streamline operations:\n- Funds will be held directly in the Committee Safe.\n- CoW DAO will act as the **ultimate beneficial owner (UBO)** of the Committee Safe.  \nThis update will improve efficiency, reduce transaction friction, and allow faster payment processing while maintaining DAO oversight.\n\n\n### Roles and Responsibilities\n\n### General Responsibilities (All Committee Members)\n- Actively participating in governance, calls, and decision-making processes.\n\n### Defined Roles\n1. **Technical Lead**  \n2. **Grant Steward**  \n3. **Grant Moderator**\n\n[...] For detailed roles descriptions please refer to the forum [post](https://forum.cow.fi/t/cip-draft-renewing-the-cow-grants-program/2771).\n\n## Compensation\n\n### Base Pay and Additional Rewards\n\n| **Role**           | **Base Pay (USD)** | **Payment in $COW Tokens** | **Bonuses** |\n|--------------------|-------------------|----------------------------|-------------|\n| **Technical Lead**  | $3,000            | Equivalent in $COW tokens   | Performance-based (peer-reviewed) |\n| **Grant Steward**   | $2,000            | Equivalent in $COW tokens   | Performance-based (peer-reviewed) |\n| **Grant Moderator** | $1,000            | Equivalent in $COW tokens   | Performance-based (peer-reviewed) |\n\n**Bonuses:** Members may submit self-assessments for exceptional contributions. Bonuses (max **1,500 xDAI/month**) are awarded quarterly after peer review, with potential external reviewer involvement.\n\n## Adding or Removing Committee Members\n\n### Adding Members\nTo address technical gaps, the DAO has discretion to add up to two additional committee members through an on-chain vote. New members will be added to the multisig as signers.\n\n### Removing Members\nCommittee members may be removed via a snapshot vote if they fail to fulfill responsibilities, including attending calls, overseeing grants, or engaging in decision-making. A 4/5 quorum is required for such votes.\n\n### CoW DAO Termination\n\nCoW DAO reserves the right to terminate and dissolve the Grants DAO with a 30-day notice period, following an on-chain vote conducted on the CoW DAO governance forum. In the event of such termination, all funds held by the CoW Grants DAO will be returned to the CoW DAO. Furthermore, the liability for any existing payouts to ongoing grantees will transfer to CoW DAO, which will assume responsibility for honoring these commitments.\n\n### Transparency and Accountability\n\nAll grant-related activities, status updates, and governance discussions can be found on the Grants Program forum section, grant tracker, and snapshot space. See the forum [post](https://forum.cow.fi/t/cip-draft-renewing-the-cow-grants-program/2771) for all relevant links.\n\nThis CIP includes a suggestion for a revised Grant Template, available [here](https://forum.cow.fi/t/proposal-for-new-grant-application-template/2768) separately on the Forum and part of this CIP and its governance process.\n\nThis CIP includes a suggestion for revised Grant Terms, available [here](https://forum.cow.fi/t/grants-dao-proposed-grant-agreement-for-grant-recipients/2752) separately on the Forum and part of this CIP and its governance process. If this CIP passes, future Grants are required to refer to these CoW DAO approved Terms.\n\nCoW DAO will be the modular owner of all GrantsDAO Safes and obtains the right to withdraw funds as per above mentioned termination, and in case of extraordinary circumstances, with no notice.\n\nNext to the possibility for the program to be terminated by CoW DAO, of course any renewal will include the success metrics of prior programs; if more funding is requested during the ongoing period, additional justification is provided.\n\n### Transaction Data\n\nNo transaction data is required.', 'dao_name': 'coW DAO'}

XBorg will provide $100,000 in XBG and an additional 100,000 USDC via the option most voted for.\n\n**Context**\n\nLast month, [XIP #21: XBG on Base](https://snapshot.box/#/s:xborg.eth/proposal/0x0407a972e8789af45fea53cb9f1db0b66138de3820648dd653c1c728663df6b9) was approved. However, due to the current market correction, the liquidity on Arbitrum has decreased significantly, and a new solution is needed to fund the initial liquidity on Base.\n\n**Options**\n\n1. Community Raise\n- Target raise: 100,000 USDC\n- Terms: 5% discount on the XBG spot price\n- Allocation: 5,000 USDC max per wallet\n- Location: xbg.xborg.com via a smart contract\n- KYC: Yes, one wallet per KYC\n- Timeframe: 7 days\n- Distribution: Once 100,000 USDC is reached or a refund occurs\n\n2. Solana Liquidity Reallocation\n- Withdraw 100,000 USDC equivalent from the XBG/SOL trading pool\n- Maintain a minimum of 70% of the current liquidity on Solana\n\n**Additional Liquidity Strategy**\n\nTo add to the initial Base liquidity, we will implement liquidity provision incentives via Aerodrome Finance, the leading DEX on Base. This will make the trading experience smoother, increase the XBG holder count and increase our awareness in the Base ecosystem.\n\n- Aerodrome $AERO incentives\n- Proprietary liquidity incentive program\n- Total expected liquidity (one-sided USDC): $1,000,000 within Q2 2025\n\n**Success Metrics**\n\nWe will view the initiative as a success if:\n\n- The initial Base liquidity is secured within a week following the end of the vote\n- There is a minimal price impact on existing XBG trading pairs\n- Base trading volume is greater than $50,000 daily average in the first month\n\n**Risks**\n\nOption 1:\n- Not reaching the target raise amount within a week following the end of the vote\n- KYC requirements could detract XBG buyers\n\nOption 2:\n- Temporarily reduced Solana liquidity could hurt the trading experience on Solana\n- Short-term XBG price impact\n\n**Implementation**\n\nThe selected option will be executed within 7 days after the vote has ended.', 'dao_name': 'N/A'}

Feb 07 03:34:53 pine-Z790-AORUS-ELITE-AX python[620557]: Thread reply created successfully: 1887782071692558841
Feb 07 03:34:53 pine-Z790-AORUS-ELITE-AX python[620557]: Tweet data saved successfully: {'tweet_id': '1887782055569752509', 'proposal_title': '[ARFC] Supply and Borrow Cap Risk Oracle Activation', 'space_id': 'aave.eth', 'proposal_description': '# Summary\n\nBuilding on the recent integration of [Aave Generalized Risk Stewards (AGRS)](https://governance.aave.com/t/arfc-aave-generalized-risk-stewards-agrs-activation/19178), this proposal introduces an automated Risk Oracle framework to enhance the efficiency of Supply and Borrow cap updates within the Aave Protocol. The framework is built around two core components: (1) algorithmic, simulation-based assessments continuously conducted to evaluate cap exposure across all markets, and (2) predefined cap utilization thresholds that trigger simulations to determine whether cap adjustments are necessary. Operating under stricter constraints than those currently permitted at the Risk Steward contract level, this system introduces no additional permissions while significantly improving the observability and responsiveness of risk management. The initial deployment is planned for Arbitrum to start, to be expanded to other chains in the future.\n\n# Motivation\n\n### Current Cap Update Process\n\nThe current implementation of the Risk Steward contract allows for the manual, periodic updating of Supply and Borrow caps, generally performed in response to market demand. Such an implementation allows for the risk/reward of respective asset exposure to be quantified and assessed in a much quicker fashion as opposed to the traditional governance mechanisms in place. This creates the ability to perform cap increases every three days by up to a 100% relative change, alongside functionality to react to adverse events or liquidity crunches through cap exposure decreases to any nominal value.\n\nWhile the implementation of the Risk Steward contract allows such risk configurations to be optimally managed in a more efficient manner, this manual integration creates significant operational overhead to maintain the state of relative demand across all Aave markets. This is currently performed through the following process:\n\n1. Manually identify a necessary cap assessment and potential alteration through internal alerting systems.\n2. Run internal supply and borrow cap risk simulations for the asset, determining the optimal increase or decrease with respect to the defined constraints at the Risk Steward level.\n3. Create a forum post outlining the imminent cap change(s) and the associated rationale for such increases through a risk report that references the state of the asset’s Aave market.\n4. Obtain the calldata and create a transaction for the cap change.\n5. Execute the cap change after a final security verification by BGD (2/2 Safe)\n\nThe high volume of updates, combined with the manual triggering of supply and borrow cap simulations, written analyses, and coordination across multiple service providers, often leads to delays in implementing cap increases. These delays can hinder potential growth opportunities for underlying assets that might otherwise contribute significantly. Additionally, the reliance on manual monitoring to address liquidity crunches for specific assets and chains adds further inefficiency. For context, since October 1, 2024, a total of 178 manual cap updates and 49 written analyses have been conducted across all instances.\n\n![image - 2025-02-03T010936.218.png](ipfs://bafkreibuloniitunlqaov72bnkc5oembjewu66dorrgnc26yzprj3hbgiu)\n### **Edge - Risk Oracle**\n\nThe Supply and Borrow Cap Risk Oracle automates the process of generating and applying cap recommendations for Aave, leveraging our underlying simulation engine being utilized today to perform manual cap changes through the Risk Steward. Depending on whether the cap utilization surpasses or falls below specific thresholds, either the cap increase or cap decrease simulation is triggered, in addition to the frequent time-based triggering of simulations for all respective markets. The simulation then determines the optimal new cap value based on a range of risk metrics. Once calculated, the updated cap is automatically published to the contract, where it is directly applied to the market, updating the cap value in real-time.\n\nThe following section provides a more detailed technical overview.\n\n- **Cap Increases**\n    - The risk oracle is triggered when the median cap utilization exceeds the defined utilization threshold for a full day.\n    - The simulation stress-tests larger supply and borrow caps, taking into account the current state of the protocol, user positions, and external factors such as liquidity availability on the chain and the general circulating supply.\n    - **Parameter Adjustments**:\n        - **Supply Cap**: Recommend a new supply cap, if the risk allows.\n        - **Borrow Cap**: Recommend a new borrow cap, constrained by its ratio to the current supply cap. If the current supply cap does not support an increase, a new supply cap will be recommended (if the risk allows) to support the new borrow cap.\n- **Cap Decreases**\n    - Decreasing cap exposure through the risk oracle is triggered with two different components of the model:\n        1. Dynamic decreases resulting from asset liquidity depreciation and/or an unhealthy set of positions within the market. The simulation stress-tests the current supply and borrow caps for all assets on a weekly cadence, taking into account the current state of the protocol, user positions, and external factors such as liquidity availability on the chain and the general circulating supply. If the current nominal cap value is deemed too risky, the simulation will determine the optimal decrease value as a function of the aforementioned components.\n        2. Deterministic decreases as a result of low cap utilization within a respective market when the monthly utilization falls below a specified threshold. To ensure a conservative approach, utilization must stay below these thresholds for at least 90% of the time. In such cases, the cap will be halved, leading to a maximum updated utilization of 50% for Supply Caps and 30% for Borrow Caps. The cap can only be reduced down to a fixed minimum value.\n    - **Parameter Adjustments**:\n        - **Supply Cap**: Recommend a new supply cap, depending on the associated risk defined in (1), and ensuring it can still support the current borrow cap in (2)\n        - **Borrow Cap**: Recommend a new borrow cap.\n- **Update Frequency**:\n    - Adjustments are made when utilization or the general market state requires it, with a minimum of 3 days between updates.\n- **Monitoring and Transparency:**\n    - All adjustments will be transparent and auditable, with data available for community review.\n\n### Risk Oracle Permissions\n\n- The risk steward contract currently enforces the following constraints:\n\n| **Parameter** | **Percent change allowed** | **minimumDelay** |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Supply Cap | +100% (increase) | 3 days |\n| Borrow Cap | +100% (increase) | 3 days |\n\nThe proposed modification to the current flow of cap updates automates the process of leveraging our currently manually utilized risk simulations to increase such caps. As such, in the proposed specification, the associated percent change allowed will be set at a more conservative +30%, with an equivalent minimum delay adhered to at the Risk Oracle level. All supply and borrow cap update events emitted can be observed in our Risk Oracle dashboard [here](https://edgebychaos.com/risk-feeds/aave). As this system will minimize the amount of manual overhead for each cap increase performed, we aim to provide periodic performance reports for the DAO.\n\nThrough the integration on Arbitrum, the following 15 markets fall under the specification:\n\n![image - 2025-02-03T010941.873.png](ipfs://bafkreieiddfslmk2up55jpwgvaxsv4zwnem3pimbv3pggsfxbi3c2jjnni)\n[Chaos Labs Arbitrum Risk Dashboard](https://community.chaoslabs.xyz/aave/risk/markets/Arbitrum-main/listed-assets)\n\n### Growth/Speculative Assets\n\nWhile the Risk Oracle is designed to establish a generalized system for automated cap increases within the proposed constraints, certain speculative, growth-oriented assets—such as ezETH on Arbitrum—cannot be standardized in this manner. These assets inherit external ad-hoc inputs, preferential considerations, and limiting risk configurations at the protocol level. As a result, the Risk Oracle will not be used to recommend cap increases for such assets. Instead, they will continue to be manually assessed using the existing method employed through the Risk Steward contract. Additionally, manual stewards will remain as a fallback mechanism when deemed necessary, ensuring continuity with the current implementation.', 'dao_name': 'Aave'}

Feb 07 05:36:15 pine-Z790-AORUS-ELITE-AX python[620557]: Tweet data saved successfully: {'tweet_id': '1887812594519425442', 'proposal_title': 'Approve the Nova Fee Sweep Action', 'space_id': 'arbitrumfoundation.eth', 'proposal_description': '## Abstract\nThe Nova Fee Sweep action applies to historical Nova transaction fees currently held in the [L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a); these fees will be swept into the DAO Treasury with the use of the modernized fee collection infrastructure outlined in the [Nova Fee Router Proposal](https://snapshot.box/#/s:arbitrumfoundation.eth/proposal/0x4ad37b12ffe5c334e0c19113ac54222983e18d36a255fbde60e483592f35fc65). The full balance of ETH–currently 1,885 ETH–will be transferred to the DAO Treasury on Arbitrum One using established smart contract infrastructure.\n\nThere will be an upcoming AIP which combines both the Timeboost AIP and the Nova Fee Sweep action AIP into a single proposal for an on-chain vote on Tally. If the on-chain vote on Tally passes successfully, Timeboost will be enabled on Arbitrum One and Arbitrum Nova and the Nova Fee Sweep action will be executed. This temperature check serves as a way for the DAO to explicitly approve for the fees from the historical [L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a) to the [ChildToParentRouter](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0x36d0170d92f66e8949eb276c3ac4fea64f83704d#code).\n\n## Motivation\nHistorically, Nova transaction fees accumulated to the [L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a) address, which required a lengthy constitutional proposal process for the ArbitrumDAO to access or spend. The successful passing of the [Nova Fee Router proposal](https://www.tally.xyz/gov/arbitrum/proposal/108288822474129076868455956066667369439381709547570289793612729242368710728616) redirected these fees to a system of "fee routers" that automatically transfers funds to the ArbitrumDAO treasury, reducing quorum requirements, reducing delays, and simplifying accounting by consolidating funds directly in the treasury. As of 28 August 2024, Nova transaction fees began accumulating to a series of RewardDistributor contracts as outlined in the Nova Fee Router proposal, streamlining the revenue collection process for the DAO.\n\nHowever, transaction fees that accumulated to the L1TimelockAlias *before* the Nova Fee Router change went into effect remain in the L1TimelockAlias, totalling 1,885.79 ETH. This proposal intends to sweep these historical Nova transaction fees from the legacy L1TimelockAlias address into the new fee collection system. This will be a one-time task because funds collected after 28 August 2024 have been, and will continue to be, automatically forwarded through the new fee collection system to the ArbitrumDAO treasury.\n\n## Key Terms\n[L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a): address that historically accumulated Nova transaction fees but was replaced by RewardDistributor contracts as a part of the [Nova Fee Router Proposal](https://snapshot.box/#/s:arbitrumfoundation.eth/proposal/0x4ad37b12ffe5c334e0c19113ac54222983e18d36a255fbde60e483592f35fc65) to upgrade the fee collection infrastructure; historical fees held by this address are the subject of this proposal. \n\n[ChildToParentRouter](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0x36d0170d92f66e8949eb276c3ac4fea64f83704d#code): smart contract that, when called, creates an L2-to-L1 message which sends the contract’s full ETH balance; once the message is executed, the ETH is transferred to a ParentToChildRouter smart contract on L1\n\n[ParentToChildRouter](https://etherscan.io/address/0x40cd7d713d7ae463f95ce5d342ea6e7f5cf7c999#code): smart contract that, when called, creates a retryable ticket which transfers the contract’s full ETH balance from L1 to the DAO Treasury on Arbitrum One\n\nThe full script for executing the Nova Fee Sweep can be found here: [Standalone Nova Fee Sweep Proposal #303](https://github.com/ArbitrumFoundation/governance/pull/303)\n\n## Steps to Implement\nThe script will be included alongside the onchain AIP which proposes for the adoption of Timeboost on Tally. Since both changes are bundled into one onchain AIP, this temperature check serves as a way for the DAO to explicitly approve for the fees from the historical [L1TimelockAlias](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0xf7951d92b0c345144506576ec13ecf5103ac905a) to the [ChildToParentRouter](https://nova.arbiscan.io/address/0x36d0170d92f66e8949eb276c3ac4fea64f83704d#code).\n\nOnce transaction fees are received by the ChildToParentRouter, the automated fee collection process will be activated, forwarding fees to the [ParentToChildRouter](https://etherscan.io/address/0x40cd7d713d7ae463f95ce5d342ea6e7f5cf7c999#code) on L1 and eventually to the [DAO Treasury](https://arbiscan.io/address/0xf3fc178157fb3c87548baa86f9d24ba38e649b58) on Arbitrum One; complete implementation details for this automated fee routing can be found in the [preceding Tally proposal](https://www.tally.xyz/gov/arbitrum/proposal/108288822474129076868455956066667369439381709547570289793612729242368710728616). Please note that Reward Distributor contracts are irrelevant for this particular action as historical fees from the L1TimelockAlias will be transferred directly to the ChildToParentRouter.\n\n## Resources and Timelines:\n[Timeboost + Nova Fee Sweep AIP forum post](https://forum.arbitrum.foundation/t/aip-timeboost-nova-fee-sweep/28247) \nNova Fee Sweep Snapshot: 30 Jan - 6 Feb\n\nThe Arbitrum Foundation will communicate a tentative date for the creation of the onchain AIP in the near future.', 'dao_name': 'Arbitrum'}
